chapters.title: The Last Chance Armada Defence Force

description:
The reason this is an introduction rather than a review is that, while other novels Ive covered have been light reads, this is a denser text. So much denser that it would require a very deep critical dive to do it justice. Its written with a great degree of care and skill, and is also completely horrific in how it sees the world. If theres enough demand, I may have to do a follow-up video offering a deeper reading, and a look at how this text has impacted the immigration debate over the decades. Let me know in the comments if youd like to see that!


This video probably would have been more timely two years ago, when the Syrian refugee crisis was in full swing, but I suspect well be hearing about it again if Climate Change has a similar impact on the movement of people.

Theres some light religion talk in this one, and none of it is designed to offend. Im talking about a very specific branch of Christianity, and while I couldnt quite find which denomination it was (I've since been told his rhetoric most closely aligns with the Society of Saint Pius X, although he isn't a member), I am not trying to present this books vision of Christianity as mainstream.

Finally, I dont remember if I mentioned it in the video, but I did not purchase this book, so no money went to Jean Raspail. Hooray!
